docs.lead_paragraph: Mrs. Sarah Cowell Le Moyne, who is home in New York after a successful tour with her new play, "The Greatest Thing in the World," says that of all the pleasant things that have been said of her recently the one she appreciated most was said in Boston. "There," she says, "they told me I resembled the wonderful Janauschek."

headline.main: Women Here and There-- Their Frills and Fancies
